(24000, 'insulin glargine and lixisenatide', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Drugs That May Decrease the Blood Glucose Lowering Effect of SOLIQUA 100/33 Drugs: Atypical antipsychotics (e.g., olanzapine and clozapine), corticosteroids, danazol, diuretics, estrogens, glucagon, isoniazid, niacin, oral contraceptives, phenothiazines, progestogens (e.g., in oral contraceptives), protease inhibitors, somatropin, sympathomimetic agents (e.g., albuterol, epinephrine, terbutaline), and thyroid hormones.', 'DailyMed'),
